header.gameNote: BIG SOUTH TOURNAMENT AT HIGH POINT

article.headline: High Point 90, Radford 73
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Jefferson scored 22 points to lead six High Point players in double figures Tuesday as the Panthers defeated Radford 90-73 in the first round of the Big South Conference tournament. Eugene Harris had 15 points and Jerald Minnis scored 12 points for High Point (22-9), the No. 2 seed. Landon Quick and Troy Bowen added 11 points each, while Arizona Reid chipped in 10 points. The Panthers advance to the semifinals Thursday against VMI, which defeated Liberty 79-78 on Tuesday. High Point was ahead 37-23 at the break and extended its lead to a 20-point margin at 48-28 with 16:40 remaining. High Point led by as many as 24 points until Radford closed the gap to 77-64 with 1:58 left to play, but the Highlanders would get no closer. A total of 57 personal fouls were called in the game, and the teams combined for 67 free throw attempts. The loss ended the season for seventh-seeded Radford (8-22), which hasn't won a Big South tournament game since 2003. Amir Johnson's led four Radford players in double figures with a game-high 23 points. Reggie McIntyre finished his college career with a double-double, netting 16 points and grabbing 11 rebounds, while Chris Oliver scored 14 points and Kenny Thomas added 12.
